\begin{align*}
(-4x + 8y - 6z) - (-4x - y - 8z) &= 16 - 10 \\
8y - 6z + y + 8z &= 6 \\
9y + 2z &= 6 \quad \text{(3)}
\end{align*}

Next, we'll solve for $y$ in terms of $z$:
\begin{align*}
9y &= 6 - 2z \\
y &= \frac{6 - 2z}{9} \quad \text{(4)}
\end{align*}

Now substitute equation (4) into the second original equation:
\begin{align*}
-4x - \left(\frac{6 - 2z}{9}\right) - 8z &= 10 \\
-36x - (6 - 2z) - 72z &= 90 \\
