-36x - 70z &= 96 \quad \text{(5)}
\end{align*}

Divide equation (5) by -2 to simplify:
\begin{align*}
18x + 35z &= -48 \quad \text{(6)}
\end{align*}

Now, we have a system of two equations with two variables:
\begin{align*}
9y + 2z &= 6 \quad \text{(3)} \\
18x + 35z &= -48 \quad \text{(6)}
\end{align*}

We can multiply equation (3) by 9 to eliminate $y$:
\begin{align*}
81y + 18z &= 54 \quad \text{(7)}
\end{align*}

Subtract equation (6) from equation (7) to solve for $z$:
\begin{align*}
(81y + 18z) - (18x + 35z) &= 54 - (-48) \\
81y + 18z - 18x - 35z &= 54 + 48 \\
81y - 18x - 17z &= 102 \quad \text{(8)}
\end{align*}

Substitute equation (4) into equation (8) for $y$:
\begin{align*}
81\left(\frac{6 - 2z}{9}\right) - 18x - 17z &= 102 \\
9(6 - 2z) - 18x - 17z &= 102 \\
54 - 18z - 18x - 17z &= 102 \\
-35z - 18x &= 48
\end{align*}

Now, we have a system of two equations with two variables:
\begin{align*}
18x + 35z &= -48 \quad \text{(6)} \\
-35z - 18x &= 48 \quad \text{(9)}
\end{align*}

Add equations (6) and (9) to solve for $z$:
\begin{align*}
(18x + 35z) + (-35z - 18x) &= -48 + 48 \\
18x - 18x + 35z - 35z &= 0 \\
0 &= 0
\end{align*}

This implies that $z$ can be any value. However, since we have $z = 0$ from the previous steps, we'll use that value. Now, substitute $z = 0$ into equation (4) to find $y$:
\begin{align*}
